From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 15:59:48 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] mf: stabilize media session and media engine playback
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Update the MF clock/session/topology, EVR presenter, MediaEngine, MFPlat buffer, and work queue behavior used by the winedmo replacement path.

This removes several SteamGameId-style assumptions by making the generic path handle the cases we tested:

- I Can't Win Against Those Pretty Girls [我打不过漂亮的她们] can recover from tiny seeks and repeated pause/play through generic MediaEngine seek coalescing instead of a hard-coded skip path.

- RE7 and Metal Gear Solid V now rely on Valve's upstream 2D-buffer write support instead of carrying the old low-copy SteamGameId hack.

- Oddworld: Abe's Oddysee no longer needs winetricks overrides for its video path; the video that previously hung now advances through the generic MediaEngine and presentation-clock path.

- Oddworld: Munch's Oddysee no longer needs winetricks overrides for its video path; the upside-down rendering case is handled by the generic presentation/frame metadata path.

- Not For Broadcast keeps interactive video/session transitions aligned with the generic MediaEngine timing path.

- Sky: Children of the Light streaming theater audio remains stable by keeping media session timing and sample delivery consistent.

- Atelier Marie Remake's pre-menu video no longer slows into a stutter after startup.

- Life Makeover and other video-frame users keep stable sample/buffer attributes needed by the downstream renderer.

The EVR changes also keep presenter state, sample release, and frame scheduling aligned with the new decoder/source-reader timing model.
